Our application uses Google maps API to recreate some of the functionality of Google Maps. This includes the maps API for displaying a map and the directions API for instructing the user where they need to drive. This article describes the process of implementing these features in an Android application. 

https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/android-sdk/start



Highest layer: Android XML files. These define the UI and appearance of the application. 
Next layer: Android Java files. These define the bahavior of the screens. 
Next layer: Database. To retrieve information about user accounts and parking availability. 

